    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:452px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Osculating Circle</text> has the same <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Radius-of-Curvature</text> as a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">point</text> on a curve and it is tangent to the curve. (Kinematically, it has at least 3 points of contact).</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A different word for &apos;osculating&apos; is <text style="font-style:italic;">&apos;kissing&apos;</text>. That is not a term often used between engineers!</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
